I concluded that this program is still fine, but I failed to keep up my good work in the midst of recovery, Dr. and PT appts., and in general having a post-op. that, though progressing well, lessened my interest, excitement, and ability to faithfully do the planning, recording and exercises needing to be done in this program.

I watched the first three  videos and started doing the program, but was not able to follow through. I filled out part of one week in the booklet, and wasn't able to keep up with it. The videos I did watch were extremely informative and I started practicing the techniques. After doing them for 2-3 weeks (with only minor consistency) I do believe that my symptoms of feeling sudden urges to get to the bathroom were cut down.    Due to my lack of focus because of the numerous things going on in my world, I unintentionally stopped doing the exercises regularly, and now find that I am back to square one, and having times when it's a struggle to get to the bathroom on time.     I hope to be able to watch the videos again and restart, as I did see benefits.    I hope my information is helpful in some way, and I apologize for not completing the program in full. I was excited to be part of the study, and hoped that I would benefit by what I learned and also wanted to contribute to the study to help others. Thank you for doing this important study. I hope many will benefit from it.
